[The complement-fixation test usually can sort out which dengue serotype
was responsible for the infection, even in instances of secondary
infections, and is an easy and inexpensive test to conduct. I wonder why
this excellent test has gone out of fashion, to be replaced by less useful
and more complex assays. - Mod.CHC
